# NodeStay Project Overview

## Purpose

A Web3 two-sided marketplace for Japanese internet cafes (インターネットカフェ), using JPYC (JPY stablecoin) on Polygon for payments and settlements.

## Core Business

1. **Seat Access Rights Market** — Users purchase AccessPassNFT with JPYC, scan to check in at a venue, and get auto-charged on checkout
2. **Idle Compute Market** — Internet cafe PCs/GPUs are rented out as compute nodes; revenue is split 75% (venue) / 25% (platform)

## Monorepo Structure (npm workspaces)

```
apps/
  web/          → Next.js 14 (App Router) frontend, port 3000
  api/          → NestJS 10 backend, port 3001
packages/
  contracts/    → Hardhat + Solidity 0.8.26 smart contracts
  domain/       → Zod schema shared types (venue, session, compute, money, etc.)
  api-client/   → NodeStayClient HTTP client wrapper
```

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Frontend | Next.js 14, React, Tailwind CSS v4 |
| Backend | NestJS 10, TypeScript 5.6+ |
| Contracts | Solidity 0.8.26, Hardhat 2.22, OpenZeppelin 5 |
| Chain | Polygon PoS (137) / Amoy testnet (80002) |
| Typings | TypeChain (ethers-v6) |
| Validation | Zod 3.24 |
| Infrastructure | PostgreSQL 16, Redis 7 (docker-compose) |

## Key Conventions

- UI copy, API messages, and code comments are in **Japanese**
- Monetary fields use the `Minor` suffix for smallest currency unit (1 JPYC = 1 minor)
- ID prefixes identify entity types: `venue_`, `plan_`, `pass_`, `sess_`, `node_`, `job_`, `disp_`, `idv_`, `ltx_`
- Idempotent operations require an `Idempotency-Key` request header
- The API currently uses in-memory Map storage (MVP); PostgreSQL/Redis integration points are prepared

## Common Commands

```bash
npm run dev          # Start API + Web concurrently
npm run build        # Build all workspaces
npm run test         # Run all tests
npm run typecheck    # Global type checking
```
